2395 rtx pat, old_trial;
2396
2397 /* If we have passed a label, we no longer own this thread. */
2398 if (LABEL_P (trial))
2399 {
2400 own_thread = 0;
2401 continue;
2402 }
2403
2404 pat = PATTERN (trial);
2405 if (GET_CODE (pat) == USE || GET_CODE (pat) == CLOBBER)
2406 continue;
2407
2408 /* If TRIAL conflicts with the insns ahead of it, we lose. Also,
2409 don't separate or copy insns that set and use CC0. */
2410 if (! insn_references_resource_p (trial, &set, true)
2411 && ! insn_sets_resource_p (trial, &set, true)
2412 && ! insn_sets_resource_p (trial, &needed, true)
2413 && (!HAVE_cc0 || (! (reg_mentioned_p (cc0_rtx, pat)
2414 && (! own_thread || ! sets_cc0_p (pat)))))
2415 && ! can_throw_internal (trial))
2416 {
2417 rtx_insn *prior_insn;
2418
2419 /* If TRIAL is redundant with some insn before INSN, we don't
2420 actually need to add it to the delay list; we can merely pretend
2421 we did. */
2422 if ((prior_insn = redundant_insn (trial, insn, *delay_list)))
2423 {
2424 fix_reg_dead_note (prior_insn, insn);
2425 if (own_thread)
2426 {
2427 update_block (trial, thread);
2428 if (trial == thread)
2429 {
2430 thread = next_active_insn (thread);
2431 if (new_thread == trial)
2432 new_thread = thread;
2433 }
2434
2435 delete_related_insns (trial);
2436 }
2437 else
2438 {
2439 update_reg_unused_notes (prior_insn, trial);
2440 new_thread = next_active_insn (trial);
2441 }
2442
2443 continue;
2444 }
2445
2446 /* There are two ways we can win: If TRIAL doesn't set anything
2447 needed at the opposite thread and can't trap, or if it can
2448 go into an annulled delay slot. But we want neither to copy
2449 nor to speculate frame-related insns. */
2450 if (!must_annul
2451 && ((condition == const_true_rtx
2452 && (own_thread || !RTX_FRAME_RELATED_P (trial)))
2453 || (! insn_sets_resource_p (trial, &opposite_needed, true)
2454 && ! may_trap_or_fault_p (pat)
2455 && ! RTX_FRAME_RELATED_P (trial))))
2456 {
2457 old_trial = trial;
2458 trial = try_split (pat, trial, 0);
2459 if (new_thread == old_trial)
2460 new_thread = trial;
2461 if (thread == old_trial)
2462 thread = trial;
2463 pat = PATTERN (trial);
2464 if (eligible_for_delay (insn, *pslots_filled, trial, flags))
2465 goto winner;
2466 }
2467 else if (!RTX_FRAME_RELATED_P (trial)
2468 && ((ANNUL_IFTRUE_SLOTS && ! thread_if_true)
2469 || (ANNUL_IFFALSE_SLOTS && thread_if_true)))
2470 {
2471 old_trial = trial;
2472 trial = try_split (pat, trial, 0);
2473 if (new_thread == old_trial)
2474 new_thread = trial;
2475 if (thread == old_trial)
2476 thread = trial;
2477 pat = PATTERN (trial);
2478 if ((must_annul || delay_list->is_empty ()) && (thread_if_true
2479 ? check_annul_list_true_false (0, *delay_list)
2480 && eligible_for_annul_false (insn, *pslots_filled, trial, flags)
2481 : check_annul_list_true_false (1, *delay_list)
2482 && eligible_for_annul_true (insn, *pslots_filled, trial, flags)))
2483 {
2484 rtx_insn *temp;
2485
2486 must_annul = 1;
2487 winner:
2488
2489 if (HAVE_cc0 && reg_mentioned_p (cc0_rtx, pat))
2490 link_cc0_insns (trial);
2491
2492 /* If we own this thread, delete the insn. If this is the
2493 destination of a branch, show that a basic block status
2494 may have been updated. In any case, mark the new
2495 starting point of this thread. */
2496 if (own_thread)
2497 {
2498 rtx note;
2499
2500 update_block (trial, thread);
2501 if (trial == thread)
2502 {
2503 thread = next_active_insn (thread);
2504 if (new_thread == trial)
2505 new_thread = thread;
2506 }
2507
2508 /* We are moving this insn, not deleting it. We must
2509 temporarily increment the use count on any referenced
2510 label lest it be deleted by delete_related_insns. */
2511 for (note = REG_NOTES (trial);
2512 note != NULL_RTX;
2513 note = XEXP (note, 1))
2514 if (REG_NOTE_KIND (note) == REG_LABEL_OPERAND
2515 || REG_NOTE_KIND (note) == REG_LABEL_TARGET)
2516 {
2517 /* REG_LABEL_OPERAND could be
2518 NOTE_INSN_DELETED_LABEL too. */
2519 if (LABEL_P (XEXP (note, 0)))
2520 LABEL_NUSES (XEXP (note, 0))++;
2521 else
2522 gcc_assert (REG_NOTE_KIND (note)
2523 == REG_LABEL_OPERAND);
2524 }
2525 if (jump_to_label_p (trial))
2526 LABEL_NUSES (JUMP_LABEL (trial))++;
2527
2528 delete_related_insns (trial);
2529
2530 for (note = REG_NOTES (trial);
2531 note != NULL_RTX;
2532 note = XEXP (note, 1))
2533 if (REG_NOTE_KIND (note) == REG_LABEL_OPERAND
2534 || REG_NOTE_KIND (note) == REG_LABEL_TARGET)
2535 {
2536 /* REG_LABEL_OPERAND could be
2537 NOTE_INSN_DELETED_LABEL too. */
2538 if (LABEL_P (XEXP (note, 0)))
2539 LABEL_NUSES (XEXP (note, 0))--;
2540 else
2541 gcc_assert (REG_NOTE_KIND (note)
2542 == REG_LABEL_OPERAND);
2543 }
2544 if (jump_to_label_p (trial))
2545 LABEL_NUSES (JUMP_LABEL (trial))--;
2546 }
2547 else
2548 new_thread = next_active_insn (trial);
2549
2550 temp = own_thread ? trial : copy_delay_slot_insn (trial);
2551 if (thread_if_true)
2552 INSN_FROM_TARGET_P (temp) = 1;
2553
2554 add_to_delay_list (temp, delay_list);
2555
2556 if (slots_to_fill == ++(*pslots_filled))
2557 {
2558 /* Even though we have filled all the slots, we
2559 may be branching to a location that has a
2560 redundant insn. Skip any if so. */
2561 while (new_thread && ! own_thread
2562 && ! insn_sets_resource_p (new_thread, &set, true)
2563 && ! insn_sets_resource_p (new_thread, &needed,
2564 true)
2565 && ! insn_references_resource_p (new_thread,
2566 &set, true)
2567 && (prior_insn
2568 = redundant_insn (new_thread, insn,
2569 *delay_list)))
2570 {
2571 /* We know we do not own the thread, so no need
2572 to call update_block and delete_insn. */
2573 fix_reg_dead_note (prior_insn, insn);
2574 update_reg_unused_notes (prior_insn, new_thread);
2575 new_thread
2576 = next_active_insn (as_a<rtx_insn *> (new_thread));
2577 }
2578 break;
2579 }
2580
2581 continue;
2582 }
2583 }
2584 }
2585
2586 /* This insn can't go into a delay slot. */
2587 lose = 1;
2588 mark_set_resources (trial, &set, 0, MARK_SRC_DEST_CALL);
2589 mark_referenced_resources (trial, &needed, true);
2590
2591 /* Ensure we don't put insns between the setting of cc and the comparison
2592 by moving a setting of cc into an earlier delay slot since these insns
2593 could clobber the condition code. */
2594 set.cc = 1;
2595
2596 /* If this insn is a register-register copy and the next insn has
2597 a use of our destination, change it to use our source. That way,
2598 it will become a candidate for our delay slot the next time
2599 through this loop. This case occurs commonly in loops that
2600 scan a list.
2601
2602 We could check for more complex cases than those tested below,
2603 but it doesn't seem worth it. It might also be a good idea to try
2604 to swap the two insns. That might do better.
2605
2606 We can't do this if the next insn modifies our destination, because
2607 that would make the replacement into the insn invalid. We also can't
2608 do this if it modifies our source, because it might be an earlyclobber
2609 operand. This latter test also prevents updating the contents of
2610 a PRE_INC. We also can't do this if there's overlap of source and
2611 destination. Overlap may happen for larger-than-register-size modes. */
2612
2613 if (NONJUMP_INSN_P (trial) && GET_CODE (pat) == SET
2614 && REG_P (SET_SRC (pat))
2615 && REG_P (SET_DEST (pat))
2616 && !reg_overlap_mentioned_p (SET_DEST (pat), SET_SRC (pat)))
2617 {
2618 rtx_insn *next = next_nonnote_insn (trial);
2619
2620 if (next && NONJUMP_INSN_P (next)
2621 && GET_CODE (PATTERN (next)) != USE
2622 && ! reg_set_p (SET_DEST (pat), next)
2623 && ! reg_set_p (SET_SRC (pat), next)
2624 && reg_referenced_p (SET_DEST (pat), PATTERN (next))
2625 && ! modified_in_p (SET_DEST (pat), next))
2626 validate_replace_rtx (SET_DEST (pat), SET_SRC (pat), next);
2627 }
2628 }
2629
2630 /* If we stopped on a branch insn that has delay slots, see if we can
2631 steal some of the insns in those slots. */
2632 if (trial && NONJUMP_INSN_P (trial)
2633 && GET_CODE (PATTERN (trial)) == SEQUENCE
2634 && JUMP_P (XVECEXP (PATTERN (trial), 0, 0)))
2635 {
2636 rtx_sequence *sequence = as_a <rtx_sequence *> (PATTERN (trial));
2637 /* If this is the `true' thread, we will want to follow the jump,
2638 so we can only do this if we have taken everything up to here. */
2639 if (thread_if_true && trial == new_thread)
2640 {
2641 steal_delay_list_from_target (insn, condition, sequence,
2642 delay_list, &set, &needed,
2643 &opposite_needed, slots_to_fill,
2644 pslots_filled, &must_annul,
2645 &new_thread);
2646 /* If we owned the thread and are told that it branched
2647 elsewhere, make sure we own the thread at the new location. */
2648 if (own_thread && trial != new_thread)
2649 own_thread = own_thread_p (new_thread, new_thread, 0);
2650 }
2651 else if (! thread_if_true)
2652 steal_delay_list_from_fallthrough (insn, condition, sequence,
2653 delay_list, &set, &needed,
2654 &opposite_needed, slots_to_fill,
2655 pslots_filled, &must_annul);
2656 }
2657
2658 /* If we haven't found anything for this delay slot and it is very
2659 likely that the branch will be taken, see if the insn at our target
2660 increments or decrements a register with an increment that does not
2661 depend on the destination register. If so, try to place the opposite
2662 arithmetic insn after the jump insn and put the arithmetic insn in the
2663 delay slot. If we can't do this, return. */
2664 if (delay_list->is_empty () && likely
2665 && new_thread && !ANY_RETURN_P (new_thread)
2666 && NONJUMP_INSN_P (new_thread)
2667 && !RTX_FRAME_RELATED_P (new_thread)
2668 && GET_CODE (PATTERN (new_thread)) != ASM_INPUT
2669 && asm_noperands (PATTERN (new_thread)) < 0)
2670 {
2671 rtx pat = PATTERN (new_thread);
2672 rtx dest;
2673 rtx src;
2674
2675 /* We know "new_thread" is an insn due to NONJUMP_INSN_P (new_thread)
2676 above. */
2677 trial = as_a <rtx_insn *> (new_thread);
2678 pat = PATTERN (trial);
2679
2680 if (!NONJUMP_INSN_P (trial)
2681 || GET_CODE (pat) != SET
2682 || ! eligible_for_delay (insn, 0, trial, flags)
2683 || can_throw_internal (trial))
2684 return;
2685
2686 dest = SET_DEST (pat), src = SET_SRC (pat);
2687 if ((GET_CODE (src) == PLUS || GET_CODE (src) == MINUS)
2688 && rtx_equal_p (XEXP (src, 0), dest)
2689 && (!FLOAT_MODE_P (GET_MODE (src))
2690 || flag_unsafe_math_optimizations)
2691 && ! reg_overlap_mentioned_p (dest, XEXP (src, 1))
2692 && ! side_effects_p (pat))
2693 {
2694 rtx other = XEXP (src, 1);
2695 rtx new_arith;
2696 rtx_insn *ninsn;
2697
2698 /* If this is a constant adjustment, use the same code with
2699 the negated constant. Otherwise, reverse the sense of the
2700 arithmetic. */
2701 if (CONST_INT_P (other))
2702 new_arith = gen_rtx_fmt_ee (GET_CODE (src), GET_MODE (src), dest,
2703 negate_rtx (GET_MODE (src), other));
2704 else
2705 new_arith = gen_rtx_fmt_ee (GET_CODE (src) == PLUS ? MINUS : PLUS,
2706 GET_MODE (src), dest, other);
2707
2708 ninsn = emit_insn_after (gen_rtx_SET (dest, new_arith), insn);
2709
2710 if (recog_memoized (ninsn) < 0
2711 || (extract_insn (ninsn),
2712 !constrain_operands (1, get_preferred_alternatives (ninsn))))
2713 {
2714 delete_related_insns (ninsn);
2715 return;
2716 }
2717
2718 if (own_thread)
2719 {
2720 update_block (trial, thread);
2721 if (trial == thread)
2722 {
2723 thread = next_active_insn (thread);
2724 if (new_thread == trial)
2725 new_thread = thread;
2726 }
2727 delete_related_insns (trial);
2728 }
2729 else
2730 new_thread = next_active_insn (trial);
2731
2732 ninsn = own_thread ? trial : copy_delay_slot_insn (trial);
2733 if (thread_if_true)
2734 INSN_FROM_TARGET_P (ninsn) = 1;
2735
2736 add_to_delay_list (ninsn, delay_list);
2737 (*pslots_filled)++;
2738 }
2739 }
2740
2741 if (!delay_list->is_empty () && must_annul)
2742 INSN_ANNULLED_BRANCH_P (insn) = 1;
2743
2744 /* If we are to branch into the middle of this thread, find an appropriate
2745 label or make a new one if none, and redirect INSN to it. If we hit the
2746 end of the function, use the end-of-function label. */
2747 if (new_thread != thread)
2748 {
2749 rtx label;
2750 bool crossing = false;
2751
2752 gcc_assert (thread_if_true);
2753
2754 if (new_thread && simplejump_or_return_p (new_thread)
2755 && redirect_with_delay_list_safe_p (insn,
2756 JUMP_LABEL (new_thread),
2757 *delay_list))
2758 new_thread = follow_jumps (JUMP_LABEL (new_thread), insn,
2759 &crossing);
2760
2761 if (ANY_RETURN_P (new_thread))
2762 label = find_end_label (new_thread);
2763 else if (LABEL_P (new_thread))
2764 label = new_thread;
2765 else
2766 label = get_label_before (as_a <rtx_insn *> (new_thread),
2767 JUMP_LABEL (insn));
2768
2769 if (label)
2770 {
2771 reorg_redirect_jump (insn, label);
2772 if (crossing)
2773 CROSSING_JUMP_P (insn) = 1;
2774 }
2775 }
2776}
2777
2778/* Make another attempt to find insns to place in delay slots.
2779
2780 We previously looked for insns located in front of the delay insn
2781 and, for non-jump delay insns, located behind the delay insn.
2782
2783 Here only try to schedule jump insns and try to move insns from either
2784 the target or the following insns into the delay slot. If annulling is
2785 supported, we will be likely to do this. Otherwise, we can do this only
2786 if safe. */
2787
2788static void
2789fill_eager_delay_slots (void)
2790{
2791 rtx_insn *insn;
2792 int i;
2793 int num_unfilled_slots = unfilled_slots_next - unfilled_slots_base;
2794
2795 for (i = 0; i < num_unfilled_slots; i++)
2796 {
2797 rtx condition;
2798 rtx target_label, insn_at_target;
2799 rtx_insn *fallthrough_insn;
2800 auto_vec<rtx_insn *, 5> delay_list;
2801 rtx_jump_insn *jump_insn;
2802 int own_target;
2803 int own_fallthrough;
2804 int prediction, slots_to_fill, slots_filled;
2805
2806 insn = unfilled_slots_base[i];
2807 if (insn == 0
2808 || insn->deleted ()
2809 || ! (jump_insn = dyn_cast <rtx_jump_insn *> (insn))
2810 || ! (condjump_p (jump_insn) || condjump_in_parallel_p (jump_insn)))
2811 continue;
2812
2813 slots_to_fill = num_delay_slots (jump_insn);
2814 /* Some machine description have defined instructions to have
2815 delay slots only in certain circumstances which may depend on
2816 nearby insns (which change due to reorg's actions).
2817
2818 For example, the PA port normally has delay slots for unconditional
2819 jumps.
2820
2821 However, the PA port claims such jumps do not have a delay slot
2822 if they are immediate successors of certain CALL_INSNs. This
2823 allows the port to favor filling the delay slot of the call with
2824 the unconditional jump. */
2825 if (slots_to_fill == 0)
2826 continue;
2827
2828 slots_filled = 0;
2829 target_label = JUMP_LABEL (jump_insn);
2830 condition = get_branch_condition (jump_insn, target_label);
2831
2832 if (condition == 0)
2833 continue;
2834
2835 /* Get the next active fallthrough and target insns and see if we own
2836 them. Then see whether the branch is likely true. We don't need
2837 to do a lot of this for unconditional branches. */
2838
2839 insn_at_target = first_active_target_insn (target_label);
2840 own_target = own_thread_p (target_label, target_label, 0);
2841
2842 if (condition == const_true_rtx)
2843 {
2844 own_fallthrough = 0;
2845 fallthrough_insn = 0;
2846 prediction = 2;
2847 }
2848 else
2849 {
2850 fallthrough_insn = next_active_insn (jump_insn);
2851 own_fallthrough = own_thread_p (NEXT_INSN (jump_insn), NULL_RTX, 1);
2852 prediction = mostly_true_jump (jump_insn);
2853 }
2854
2855 /* If this insn is expected to branch, first try to get insns from our
2856 target, then our fallthrough insns. If it is not expected to branch,
2857 try the other order. */
2858
2859 if (prediction > 0)
2860 {
2861 fill_slots_from_thread (jump_insn, condition, insn_at_target,
2862 fallthrough_insn, prediction == 2, 1,
2863 own_target,
2864 slots_to_fill, &slots_filled, &delay_list);
2865
2866 if (delay_list.is_empty () && own_fallthrough)
2867 {
2868 /* Even though we didn't find anything for delay slots,
2869 we might have found a redundant insn which we deleted
2870 from the thread that was filled. So we have to recompute
2871 the next insn at the target. */
2872 target_label = JUMP_LABEL (jump_insn);
2873 insn_at_target = first_active_target_insn (target_label);
2874
2875 fill_slots_from_thread (jump_insn, condition, fallthrough_insn,
2876 insn_at_target, 0, 0, own_fallthrough,
2877 slots_to_fill, &slots_filled,
2878 &delay_list);
2879 }
2880 }
2881 else
2882 {
2883 if (own_fallthrough)
2884 fill_slots_from_thread (jump_insn, condition, fallthrough_insn,
2885 insn_at_target, 0, 0, own_fallthrough,
2886 slots_to_fill, &slots_filled, &delay_list);
2887
2888 if (delay_list.is_empty ())
2889 fill_slots_from_thread (jump_insn, condition, insn_at_target,
2890 next_active_insn (insn), 0, 1, own_target,
2891 slots_to_fill, &slots_filled, &delay_list);
2892 }
2893
2894 if (!delay_list.is_empty ())
2895 unfilled_slots_base[i]
2896 = emit_delay_sequence (jump_insn, delay_list, slots_filled);
2897
2898 if (slots_to_fill == slots_filled)
2899 unfilled_slots_base[i] = 0;
2900
2901 note_delay_statistics (slots_filled, 1);
2902 }
2903}
2904
2905static void delete_computation (rtx_insn *insn);
2906
2907/* Recursively delete prior insns that compute the value (used only by INSN
2908 which the caller is deleting) stored in the register mentioned by NOTE
2909 which is a REG_DEAD note associated with INSN. */
2910
2911static void
2912delete_prior_computation (rtx note, rtx_insn *insn)
2913{
2914 rtx_insn *our_prev;
2915 rtx reg = XEXP (note, 0);
2916
2917 for (our_prev = prev_nonnote_insn (insn);
2918 our_prev && (NONJUMP_INSN_P (our_prev)
2919 || CALL_P (our_prev));
2920 our_prev = prev_nonnote_insn (our_prev))
2921 {
2922 rtx pat = PATTERN (our_prev);
2923
2924 /* If we reach a CALL which is not calling a const function
2925 or the callee pops the arguments, then give up. */
2926 if (CALL_P (our_prev)
2927 && (! RTL_CONST_CALL_P (our_prev)
2928 || GET_CODE (pat) != SET || GET_CODE (SET_SRC (pat)) != CALL))
2929 break;
2930
2931 /* If we reach a SEQUENCE, it is too complex to try to
2932 do anything with it, so give up. We can be run during
2933 and after reorg, so SEQUENCE rtl can legitimately show
2934 up here. */
2935 if (GET_CODE (pat) == SEQUENCE)
2936 break;
2937
2938 if (GET_CODE (pat) == USE
2939 && NONJUMP_INSN_P (XEXP (pat, 0)))
2940 /* reorg creates USEs that look like this. We leave them
2941 alone because reorg needs them for its own purposes. */
2942 break;
2943
2944 if (reg_set_p (reg, pat))
2945 {
2946 if (side_effects_p (pat) && !CALL_P (our_prev))
2947 break;
2948
2949 if (GET_CODE (pat) == PARALLEL)
2950 {
2951 /* If we find a SET of something else, we can't
2952 delete the insn. */
2953
2954 int i;
2955
2956 for (i = 0; i < XVECLEN (pat, 0); i++)
2957 {
2958 rtx part = XVECEXP (pat, 0, i);
2959
2960 if (GET_CODE (part) == SET
2961 && SET_DEST (part) != reg)
2962 break;
2963 }
2964
2965 if (i == XVECLEN (pat, 0))
2966 delete_computation (our_prev);
2967 }
2968 else if (GET_CODE (pat) == SET
2969 && REG_P (SET_DEST (pat)))
2970 {
2971 int dest_regno = REGNO (SET_DEST (pat));
2972 int dest_endregno = END_REGNO (SET_DEST (pat));
2973 int regno = REGNO (reg);
2974 int endregno = END_REGNO (reg);
2975
2976 if (dest_regno >= regno
2977 && dest_endregno <= endregno)
2978 delete_computation (our_prev);
2979
2980 /* We may have a multi-word hard register and some, but not
2981 all, of the words of the register are needed in subsequent
2982 insns. Write REG_UNUSED notes for those parts that were not
2983 needed. */
2984 else if (dest_regno <= regno
2985 && dest_endregno >= endregno)
2986 {
2987 int i;
2988
2989 add_reg_note (our_prev, REG_UNUSED, reg);
2990
2991 for (i = dest_regno; i < dest_endregno; i++)
2992 if (! find_regno_note (our_prev, REG_UNUSED, i))
2993 break;
2994
2995 if (i == dest_endregno)
2996 delete_computation (our_prev);
2997 }
2998 }
2999
3000 break;
3001 }
3002
3003 /* If PAT references the register that dies here, it is an
3004 additional use. Hence any prior SET isn't dead. However, this
3005 insn becomes the new place for the REG_DEAD note. */
3006 if (reg_overlap_mentioned_p (reg, pat))
3007 {
3008 XEXP (note, 1) = REG_NOTES (our_prev);
3009 REG_NOTES (our_prev) = note;
3010 break;
3011 }
3012 }
3013}
3014
3015/* Delete INSN and recursively delete insns that compute values used only
3016 by INSN. This uses the REG_DEAD notes computed during flow analysis.
3017
3018 Look at all our REG_DEAD notes. If a previous insn does nothing other
3019 than set a register that dies in this insn, we can delete that insn
3020 as well.
3021
3022 On machines with CC0, if CC0 is used in this insn, we may be able to
3023 delete the insn that set it. */
3024
3025static void
3026delete_computation (rtx_insn *insn)
3027{
3028 rtx note, next;
3029
3030 if (HAVE_cc0 && reg_referenced_p (cc0_rtx, PATTERN (insn)))
3031 {
3032 rtx_insn *prev = prev_nonnote_insn (insn);
3033 /* We assume that at this stage
3034 CC's are always set explicitly
3035 and always immediately before the jump that
3036 will use them. So if the previous insn
3037 exists to set the CC's, delete it
3038 (unless it performs auto-increments, etc.). */
3039 if (prev && NONJUMP_INSN_P (prev)
3040 && sets_cc0_p (PATTERN (prev)))
3041 {
3042 if (sets_cc0_p (PATTERN (prev)) > 0
3043 && ! side_effects_p (PATTERN (prev)))
3044 delete_computation (prev);
3045 else
3046 /* Otherwise, show that cc0 won't be used. */
3047 add_reg_note (prev, REG_UNUSED, cc0_rtx);
3048 }
3049 }
3050
3051 for (note = REG_NOTES (insn); note; note = next)
3052 {
3053 next = XEXP (note, 1);
3054
3055 if (REG_NOTE_KIND (note) != REG_DEAD
3056 /* Verify that the REG_NOTE is legitimate. */
3057 || !REG_P (XEXP (note, 0)))
3058 continue;
3059
3060 delete_prior_computation (note, insn);
3061 }
3062
3063 delete_related_insns (insn);
3064}
3065
3066/* If all INSN does is set the pc, delete it,
3067 and delete the insn that set the condition codes for it
3068 if that's what the previous thing was. */
3069
3070static void
3071delete_jump (rtx_insn *insn)
3072{
3073 rtx set = single_set (insn);
3074
3075 if (set && GET_CODE (SET_DEST (set)) == PC)
3076 delete_computation (insn);
3077}
3078
3079static rtx_insn *
3080label_before_next_insn (rtx_insn *x, rtx scan_limit)
3081{
3082 rtx_insn *insn = next_active_insn (x);
3083 while (insn)
3084 {
3085 insn = PREV_INSN (insn);
3086 if (insn == scan_limit || insn == NULL_RTX)
3087 return NULL;
3088 if (LABEL_P (insn))
3089 break;
3090 }
3091 return insn;
3092}

3094/* Return TRUE if there is a NOTE_INSN_SWITCH_TEXT_SECTIONS note in between
3095 BEG and END. */
3096
3097static bool
3098switch_text_sections_between_p (const rtx_insn *beg, const rtx_insn *end)
3099{
3100 const rtx_insn *p;
3101 for (p = beg; p != end; p = NEXT_INSN (p))
3102 if (NOTE_P (p) && NOTE_KIND (p) == NOTE_INSN_SWITCH_TEXT_SECTIONS)
3103 return true;
3104 return false;
3105}

3108/* Once we have tried two ways to fill a delay slot, make a pass over the
3109 code to try to improve the results and to do such things as more jump
3110 threading. */
3111
3112static void
3113relax_delay_slots (rtx_insn *first)
3114{
3115 rtx_insn *insn, *next;
3116 rtx_sequence *pat;
3117 rtx_insn *delay_insn;
3118 rtx target_label;
3119
3120 /* Look at every JUMP_INSN and see if we can improve it. */
3121 for (insn = first; insn; insn = next)
3122 {
3123 rtx_insn *other, *prior_insn;
3124 bool crossing;
3125
3126 next = next_active_insn (insn);
3127
3128 /* If this is a jump insn, see if it now jumps to a jump, jumps to
3129 the next insn, or jumps to a label that is not the last of a
3130 group of consecutive labels. */
3131 if (is_a <rtx_jump_insn *> (insn)
3132 && (condjump_p (insn) || condjump_in_parallel_p (insn))
3133 && !ANY_RETURN_P (target_label = JUMP_LABEL (insn)))
3134 {
3135 rtx_jump_insn *jump_insn = as_a <rtx_jump_insn *> (insn);
3136 target_label
3137 = skip_consecutive_labels (follow_jumps (target_label, jump_insn,
3138 &crossing));
3139 if (ANY_RETURN_P (target_label))
3140 target_label = find_end_label (target_label);
3141
3142 if (target_label
3143 && next_active_insn (as_a<rtx_insn *> (target_label)) == next
3144 && ! condjump_in_parallel_p (jump_insn)
3145 && ! (next && switch_text_sections_between_p (jump_insn, next)))
3146 {
3147 delete_jump (jump_insn);
3148 continue;
3149 }
3150
3151 if (target_label && target_label != JUMP_LABEL (jump_insn))
3152 {
3153 reorg_redirect_jump (jump_insn, target_label);
3154 if (crossing)
3155 CROSSING_JUMP_P (jump_insn) = 1;
3156 }
3157
3158 /* See if this jump conditionally branches around an unconditional
3159 jump. If so, invert this jump and point it to the target of the
3160 second jump. Check if it's possible on the target. */
3161 if (next && simplejump_or_return_p (next)
3162 && any_condjump_p (jump_insn)
3163 && target_label
3164 && (next_active_insn (as_a<rtx_insn *> (target_label))
3165 == next_active_insn (next))
3166 && no_labels_between_p (jump_insn, next)
3167 && targetm.can_follow_jump (jump_insn, next))
3168 {
3169 rtx label = JUMP_LABEL (next);
3170
3171 /* Be careful how we do this to avoid deleting code or
3172 labels that are momentarily dead. See similar optimization
3173 in jump.c.
3174
3175 We also need to ensure we properly handle the case when
3176 invert_jump fails. */
3177
3178 ++LABEL_NUSES (target_label);
3179 if (!ANY_RETURN_P (label))
3180 ++LABEL_NUSES (label);
3181
3182 if (invert_jump (jump_insn, label, 1))
3183 {
3184 delete_related_insns (next);
3185 next = jump_insn;
3186 }
3187
3188 if (!ANY_RETURN_P (label))
3189 --LABEL_NUSES (label);
3190
3191 if (--LABEL_NUSES (target_label) == 0)
3192 delete_related_insns (target_label);
3193
3194 continue;
3195 }
3196 }
3197
3198 /* If this is an unconditional jump and the previous insn is a
3199 conditional jump, try reversing the condition of the previous
3200 insn and swapping our targets. The next pass might be able to
3201 fill the slots.
3202
3203 Don't do this if we expect the conditional branch to be true, because
3204 we would then be making the more common case longer. */
3205
3206 if (simplejump_or_return_p (insn)
3207 && (other = prev_active_insn (insn)) != 0
3208 && any_condjump_p (other)
3209 && no_labels_between_p (other, insn)
3210 && 0 > mostly_true_jump (other))
3211 {
3212 rtx other_target = JUMP_LABEL (other);
3213 target_label = JUMP_LABEL (insn);
3214
3215 if (invert_jump (as_a <rtx_jump_insn *> (other), target_label, 0))
3216 reorg_redirect_jump (as_a <rtx_jump_insn *> (insn), other_target);
3217 }
3218
3219 /* Now look only at cases where we have a filled delay slot. */
3220 if (!NONJUMP_INSN_P (insn) || GET_CODE (PATTERN (insn)) != SEQUENCE)
3221 continue;
3222
3223 pat = as_a <rtx_sequence *> (PATTERN (insn));
3224 delay_insn = pat->insn (0);
3225
3226 /* See if the first insn in the delay slot is redundant with some
3227 previous insn. Remove it from the delay slot if so; then set up
3228 to reprocess this insn. */
3229 if ((prior_insn = redundant_insn (pat->insn (1), delay_insn, vNULL)))
3230 {
3231 fix_reg_dead_note (prior_insn, insn);
3232 update_block (pat->insn (1), insn);
3233 delete_from_delay_slot (pat->insn (1));
3234 next = prev_active_insn (next);
3235 continue;
3236 }
3237
3238 /* See if we have a RETURN insn with a filled delay slot followed
3239 by a RETURN insn with an unfilled a delay slot. If so, we can delete
3240 the first RETURN (but not its delay insn). This gives the same
3241 effect in fewer instructions.
3242
3243 Only do so if optimizing for size since this results in slower, but
3244 smaller code. */
3245 if (optimize_function_for_size_p (cfun)
3246 && ANY_RETURN_P (PATTERN (delay_insn))
3247 && next
3248 && JUMP_P (next)
3249 && PATTERN (next) == PATTERN (delay_insn))
3250 {
3251 rtx_insn *after;
3252 int i;
3253
3254 /* Delete the RETURN and just execute the delay list insns.
3255
3256 We do this by deleting the INSN containing the SEQUENCE, then
3257 re-emitting the insns separately, and then deleting the RETURN.
3258 This allows the count of the jump target to be properly
3259 decremented.
3260
3261 Note that we need to change the INSN_UID of the re-emitted insns
3262 since it is used to hash the insns for mark_target_live_regs and
3263 the re-emitted insns will no longer be wrapped up in a SEQUENCE.
3264
3265 Clear the from target bit, since these insns are no longer
3266 in delay slots. */
3267 for (i = 0; i < XVECLEN (pat, 0); i++)
3268 INSN_FROM_TARGET_P (XVECEXP (pat, 0, i)) = 0;
3269
3270 rtx_insn *prev = PREV_INSN (insn);
3271 delete_related_insns (insn);
3272 gcc_assert (GET_CODE (pat) == SEQUENCE);
3273 add_insn_after (delay_insn, prev, NULL);
3274 after = delay_insn;
3275 for (i = 1; i < pat->len (); i++)
3276 after = emit_copy_of_insn_after (pat->insn (i), after);
3277 delete_scheduled_jump (delay_insn);
3278 continue;
3279 }
3280
3281 /* Now look only at the cases where we have a filled JUMP_INSN. */
3282 rtx_jump_insn *delay_jump_insn =
3283 dyn_cast <rtx_jump_insn *> (delay_insn);
3284 if (! delay_jump_insn || !(condjump_p (delay_jump_insn)
3285 || condjump_in_parallel_p (delay_jump_insn)))
3286 continue;
3287
3288 target_label = JUMP_LABEL (delay_jump_insn);
3289 if (target_label && ANY_RETURN_P (target_label))
3290 continue;
3291
3292 /* If this jump goes to another unconditional jump, thread it, but
3293 don't convert a jump into a RETURN here. */
3294 rtx trial = skip_consecutive_labels (follow_jumps (target_label,
3295 delay_jump_insn,
3296 &crossing));
3297 if (ANY_RETURN_P (trial))
3298 trial = find_end_label (trial);
3299
3300 if (trial && trial != target_label
3301 && redirect_with_delay_slots_safe_p (delay_jump_insn, trial, insn))
3302 {
3303 reorg_redirect_jump (delay_jump_insn, trial);
3304 target_label = trial;
3305 if (crossing)
3306 CROSSING_JUMP_P (delay_jump_insn) = 1;
3307 }
3308
3309 /* If the first insn at TARGET_LABEL is redundant with a previous
3310 insn, redirect the jump to the following insn and process again.
3311 We use next_real_insn instead of next_active_insn so we
3312 don't skip USE-markers, or we'll end up with incorrect
3313 liveness info. */
3314 trial = next_real_insn (target_label);
3315 if (trial && GET_CODE (PATTERN (trial)) != SEQUENCE
3316 && redundant_insn (trial, insn, vNULL)
3317 && ! can_throw_internal (trial))
3318 {
3319 /* Figure out where to emit the special USE insn so we don't
3320 later incorrectly compute register live/death info. */
3321 rtx_insn *tmp = next_active_insn (as_a<rtx_insn *> (trial));
3322 if (tmp == 0)
3323 tmp = find_end_label (simple_return_rtx);
3324
3325 if (tmp)
3326 {
3327 /* Insert the special USE insn and update dataflow info.
3328 We know "trial" is an insn here as it is the output of
3329 next_real_insn () above. */
3330 update_block (as_a <rtx_insn *> (trial), tmp);
3331
3332 /* Now emit a label before the special USE insn, and
3333 redirect our jump to the new label. */
3334 target_label = get_label_before (PREV_INSN (tmp), target_label);
3335 reorg_redirect_jump (delay_jump_insn, target_label);
3336 next = insn;
3337 continue;
3338 }
3339 }
3340
3341 /* Similarly, if it is an unconditional jump with one insn in its
3342 delay list and that insn is redundant, thread the jump. */
3343 rtx_sequence *trial_seq =
3344 trial ? dyn_cast <rtx_sequence *> (PATTERN (trial)) : NULL;
3345 if (trial_seq
3346 && trial_seq->len () == 2
3347 && JUMP_P (trial_seq->insn (0))
3348 && simplejump_or_return_p (trial_seq->insn (0))
3349 && redundant_insn (trial_seq->insn (1), insn, vNULL))
3350 {
3351 target_label = JUMP_LABEL (trial_seq->insn (0));
3352 if (ANY_RETURN_P (target_label))
3353 target_label = find_end_label (target_label);
3354
3355 if (target_label
3356 && redirect_with_delay_slots_safe_p (delay_jump_insn,
3357 target_label, insn))
3358 {
3359 update_block (trial_seq->insn (1), insn);
3360 reorg_redirect_jump (delay_jump_insn, target_label);
3361 next = insn;
3362 continue;
3363 }
3364 }
3365
3366 /* See if we have a simple (conditional) jump that is useless. */
3367 if (! INSN_ANNULLED_BRANCH_P (delay_jump_insn)
3368 && ! condjump_in_parallel_p (delay_jump_insn)
3369 && prev_active_insn (as_a<rtx_insn *> (target_label)) == insn
3370 && ! BARRIER_P (prev_nonnote_insn (as_a<rtx_insn *> (target_label)))
3371 /* If the last insn in the delay slot sets CC0 for some insn,
3372 various code assumes that it is in a delay slot. We could
3373 put it back where it belonged and delete the register notes,
3374 but it doesn't seem worthwhile in this uncommon case. */

3376 || ! find_reg_note (XVECEXP (pat, 0, XVECLEN (pat, 0) - 1),
3377 REG_CC_USER, NULL_RTX)))
3378 {
3379 rtx_insn *after;
3380 int i;
3381
3382 /* All this insn does is execute its delay list and jump to the
3383 following insn. So delete the jump and just execute the delay
3384 list insns.
3385
3386 We do this by deleting the INSN containing the SEQUENCE, then
3387 re-emitting the insns separately, and then deleting the jump.
3388 This allows the count of the jump target to be properly
3389 decremented.
3390
3391 Note that we need to change the INSN_UID of the re-emitted insns
3392 since it is used to hash the insns for mark_target_live_regs and
3393 the re-emitted insns will no longer be wrapped up in a SEQUENCE.
3394
3395 Clear the from target bit, since these insns are no longer
3396 in delay slots. */
3397 for (i = 0; i < XVECLEN (pat, 0); i++)
3398 INSN_FROM_TARGET_P (XVECEXP (pat, 0, i)) = 0;
3399
3400 rtx_insn *prev = PREV_INSN (insn);
3401 delete_related_insns (insn);
3402 gcc_assert (GET_CODE (pat) == SEQUENCE);
3403 add_insn_after (delay_jump_insn, prev, NULL);
3404 after = delay_jump_insn;
3405 for (i = 1; i < pat->len (); i++)
3406 after = emit_copy_of_insn_after (pat->insn (i), after);
3407 delete_scheduled_jump (delay_jump_insn);
3408 continue;
3409 }
3410
3411 /* See if this is an unconditional jump around a single insn which is
3412 identical to the one in its delay slot. In this case, we can just
3413 delete the branch and the insn in its delay slot. */
3414 if (next && NONJUMP_INSN_P (next)
3415 && label_before_next_insn (next, insn) == target_label
3416 && simplejump_p (insn)
3417 && XVECLEN (pat, 0) == 2
3418 && rtx_equal_p (PATTERN (next), PATTERN (pat->insn (1))))
3419 {
3420 delete_related_insns (insn);
3421 continue;
3422 }
3423
3424 /* See if this jump (with its delay slots) conditionally branches
3425 around an unconditional jump (without delay slots). If so, invert
3426 this jump and point it to the target of the second jump. We cannot
3427 do this for annulled jumps, though. Again, don't convert a jump to
3428 a RETURN here. */
3429 if (! INSN_ANNULLED_BRANCH_P (delay_jump_insn)
3430 && any_condjump_p (delay_jump_insn)
3431 && next && simplejump_or_return_p (next)
3432 && (next_active_insn (as_a<rtx_insn *> (target_label))
3433 == next_active_insn (next))
3434 && no_labels_between_p (insn, next))
3435 {
3436 rtx label = JUMP_LABEL (next);
3437 rtx old_label = JUMP_LABEL (delay_jump_insn);
3438
3439 if (ANY_RETURN_P (label))
3440 label = find_end_label (label);
3441
3442 /* find_end_label can generate a new label. Check this first. */
3443 if (label
3444 && no_labels_between_p (insn, next)
3445 && redirect_with_delay_slots_safe_p (delay_jump_insn,
3446 label, insn))
3447 {
3448 /* Be careful how we do this to avoid deleting code or labels
3449 that are momentarily dead. See similar optimization in
3450 jump.c */
3451 if (old_label)
3452 ++LABEL_NUSES (old_label);
3453
3454 if (invert_jump (delay_jump_insn, label, 1))
3455 {
3456 int i;
3457
3458 /* Must update the INSN_FROM_TARGET_P bits now that
3459 the branch is reversed, so that mark_target_live_regs
3460 will handle the delay slot insn correctly. */
3461 for (i = 1; i < XVECLEN (PATTERN (insn), 0); i++)
3462 {
3463 rtx slot = XVECEXP (PATTERN (insn), 0, i);
3464 INSN_FROM_TARGET_P (slot) = ! INSN_FROM_TARGET_P (slot);
3465 }
3466
3467 delete_related_insns (next);
3468 next = insn;
3469 }
3470
3471 if (old_label && --LABEL_NUSES (old_label) == 0)
3472 delete_related_insns (old_label);
3473 continue;
3474 }
3475 }
3476
3477 /* If we own the thread opposite the way this insn branches, see if we
3478 can merge its delay slots with following insns. */
3479 if (INSN_FROM_TARGET_P (pat->insn (1))
3480 && own_thread_p (NEXT_INSN (insn), 0, 1))
3481 try_merge_delay_insns (insn, next);
3482 else if (! INSN_FROM_TARGET_P (pat->insn (1))
3483 && own_thread_p (target_label, target_label, 0))
3484 try_merge_delay_insns (insn,
3485 next_active_insn (as_a<rtx_insn *> (target_label)));
3486
3487 /* If we get here, we haven't deleted INSN. But we may have deleted
3488 NEXT, so recompute it. */
3489 next = next_active_insn (insn);
3490 }
3491}

3494/* Look for filled jumps to the end of function label. We can try to convert
3495 them into RETURN insns if the insns in the delay slot are valid for the
3496 RETURN as well. */
3497
3498static void
3499make_return_insns (rtx_insn *first)
3500{
3501 rtx_insn *insn;
3502 rtx_jump_insn *jump_insn;
3503 rtx real_return_label = function_return_label;
3504 rtx real_simple_return_label = function_simple_return_label;
3505 int slots, i;
3506
3507 /* See if there is a RETURN insn in the function other than the one we
3508 made for END_OF_FUNCTION_LABEL. If so, set up anything we can't change
3509 into a RETURN to jump to it. */
3510 for (insn = first; insn; insn = NEXT_INSN (insn))
3511 if (JUMP_P (insn) && ANY_RETURN_P (PATTERN (insn)))
3512 {
3513 rtx t = get_label_before (insn, NULL_RTX);
3514 if (PATTERN (insn) == ret_rtx)
3515 real_return_label = t;
3516 else
3517 real_simple_return_label = t;
3518 break;
3519 }
3520
3521 /* Show an extra usage of REAL_RETURN_LABEL so it won't go away if it
3522 was equal to END_OF_FUNCTION_LABEL. */
3523 if (real_return_label)
3524 LABEL_NUSES (real_return_label)++;
3525 if (real_simple_return_label)
3526 LABEL_NUSES (real_simple_return_label)++;
3527
3528 /* Clear the list of insns to fill so we can use it. */
3529 obstack_free (&unfilled_slots_obstack, unfilled_firstobj);
3530
3531 for (insn = first; insn; insn = NEXT_INSN (insn))
3532 {
3533 int flags;
3534 rtx kind, real_label;
3535
3536 /* Only look at filled JUMP_INSNs that go to the end of function
3537 label. */
3538 if (!NONJUMP_INSN_P (insn))
3539 continue;
3540
3541 if (GET_CODE (PATTERN (insn)) != SEQUENCE)
3542 continue;
3543
3544 rtx_sequence *pat = as_a <rtx_sequence *> (PATTERN (insn));
3545
3546 if (!jump_to_label_p (pat->insn (0)))
3547 continue;
3548
3549 if (JUMP_LABEL (pat->insn (0)) == function_return_label)
3550 {
3551 kind = ret_rtx;
3552 real_label = real_return_label;
3553 }
3554 else if (JUMP_LABEL (pat->insn (0)) == function_simple_return_label)
3555 {
3556 kind = simple_return_rtx;
3557 real_label = real_simple_return_label;
3558 }
3559 else
3560 continue;
3561
3562 jump_insn = as_a <rtx_jump_insn *> (pat->insn (0));
3563
3564 /* If we can't make the jump into a RETURN, try to redirect it to the best
3565 RETURN and go on to the next insn. */
3566 if (!reorg_redirect_jump (jump_insn, kind))
3567 {
3568 /* Make sure redirecting the jump will not invalidate the delay
3569 slot insns. */
3570 if (redirect_with_delay_slots_safe_p (jump_insn, real_label, insn))
3571 reorg_redirect_jump (jump_insn, real_label);
3572 continue;
3573 }
3574
3575 /* See if this RETURN can accept the insns current in its delay slot.
3576 It can if it has more or an equal number of slots and the contents
3577 of each is valid. */
3578
3579 flags = get_jump_flags (jump_insn, JUMP_LABEL (jump_insn));
3580 slots = num_delay_slots (jump_insn);
3581 if (slots >= XVECLEN (pat, 0) - 1)
3582 {
3583 for (i = 1; i < XVECLEN (pat, 0); i++)
3584 if (! (
3585#if ANNUL_IFFALSE_SLOTS
3586 (INSN_ANNULLED_BRANCH_P (jump_insn)
3587 && INSN_FROM_TARGET_P (pat->insn (i)))
3588 ? eligible_for_annul_false (jump_insn, i - 1,
3589 pat->insn (i), flags) :
3590#endif
3591#if ANNUL_IFTRUE_SLOTS
3592 (INSN_ANNULLED_BRANCH_P (jump_insn)
3593 && ! INSN_FROM_TARGET_P (pat->insn (i)))
3594 ? eligible_for_annul_true (jump_insn, i - 1,
3595 pat->insn (i), flags) :
3596#endif
3597 eligible_for_delay (jump_insn, i - 1,
3598 pat->insn (i), flags)))
3599 break;
3600 }
3601 else
3602 i = 0;
3603
3604 if (i == XVECLEN (pat, 0))
3605 continue;
3606
3607 /* We have to do something with this insn. If it is an unconditional
3608 RETURN, delete the SEQUENCE and output the individual insns,
3609 followed by the RETURN. Then set things up so we try to find
3610 insns for its delay slots, if it needs some. */
3611 if (ANY_RETURN_P (PATTERN (jump_insn)))
3612 {
3613 rtx_insn *prev = PREV_INSN (insn);
3614
3615 delete_related_insns (insn);
3616 for (i = 1; i < XVECLEN (pat, 0); i++)
3617 prev = emit_insn_after (PATTERN (XVECEXP (pat, 0, i)), prev);
3618
3619 insn = emit_jump_insn_after (PATTERN (jump_insn), prev);
3620 emit_barrier_after (insn);
3621
3622 if (slots)
3623 obstack_ptr_grow (&unfilled_slots_obstack, insn);
3624 }
3625 else
3626 /* It is probably more efficient to keep this with its current
3627 delay slot as a branch to a RETURN. */
3628 reorg_redirect_jump (jump_insn, real_label);
3629 }
3630
3631 /* Now delete REAL_RETURN_LABEL if we never used it. Then try to fill any
3632 new delay slots we have created. */
3633 if (real_return_label != NULL_RTX && --LABEL_NUSES (real_return_label) == 0)
3634 delete_related_insns (real_return_label);
3635 if (real_simple_return_label != NULL_RTX
3636 && --LABEL_NUSES (real_simple_return_label) == 0)
3637 delete_related_insns (real_simple_return_label);
3638
3639 fill_simple_delay_slots (1);
3640 fill_simple_delay_slots (0);
3641}
3642
3643/* Try to find insns to place in delay slots. */
3644
3645static void
3646dbr_schedule (rtx_insn *first)
3647{
3648 rtx_insn *insn, *next, *epilogue_insn = 0;
3649 int i;
3650 bool need_return_insns;
3651
3652 /* If the current function has no insns other than the prologue and
3653 epilogue, then do not try to fill any delay slots. */
3654 if (n_basic_blocks_for_fn (cfun) == NUM_FIXED_BLOCKS)
3655 return;
3656
3657 /* Find the highest INSN_UID and allocate and initialize our map from
3658 INSN_UID's to position in code. */
3659 for (max_uid = 0, insn = first; insn; insn = NEXT_INSN (insn))
3660 {
3661 if (INSN_UID (insn) > max_uid)
3662 max_uid = INSN_UID (insn);
3663 if (NOTE_P (insn)
3664 && NOTE_KIND (insn) == NOTE_INSN_EPILOGUE_BEG)
3665 epilogue_insn = insn;
3666 }
3667
3668 uid_to_ruid = XNEWVEC (int, max_uid + 1);
3669 for (i = 0, insn = first; insn; i++, insn = NEXT_INSN (insn))
3670 uid_to_ruid[INSN_UID (insn)] = i;
3671
3672 /* Initialize the list of insns that need filling. */
3673 if (unfilled_firstobj == 0)
3674 {
3675 gcc_obstack_init (&unfilled_slots_obstack);
3676 unfilled_firstobj = XOBNEWVAR (&unfilled_slots_obstack, rtx, 0);
3677 }
3678
3679 for (insn = next_active_insn (first); insn; insn = next_active_insn (insn))
3680 {
3681 rtx target;
3682
3683 /* Skip vector tables. We can't get attributes for them. */
3684 if (JUMP_TABLE_DATA_P (insn))
3685 continue;
3686
3687 if (JUMP_P (insn))
3688 INSN_ANNULLED_BRANCH_P (insn) = 0;
3689 INSN_FROM_TARGET_P (insn) = 0;
3690
3691 if (num_delay_slots (insn) > 0)
3692 obstack_ptr_grow (&unfilled_slots_obstack, insn);
3693
3694 /* Ensure all jumps go to the last of a set of consecutive labels. */
3695 if (JUMP_P (insn)
3696 && (condjump_p (insn) || condjump_in_parallel_p (insn))
3697 && !ANY_RETURN_P (JUMP_LABEL (insn))
3698 && ((target = skip_consecutive_labels (JUMP_LABEL (insn)))
3699 != JUMP_LABEL (insn)))
3700 redirect_jump (as_a <rtx_jump_insn *> (insn), target, 1);
3701 }
3702
3703 init_resource_info (epilogue_insn);
3704
3705 /* Show we haven't computed an end-of-function label yet. */
3706 function_return_label = function_simple_return_label = NULL;
3707
3708 /* Initialize the statistics for this function. */
3709 memset (num_insns_needing_delays, 0, sizeof num_insns_needing_delays);
3710 memset (num_filled_delays, 0, sizeof num_filled_delays);
3711
3712 /* Now do the delay slot filling. Try everything twice in case earlier
3713 changes make more slots fillable. */
3714
3715 for (reorg_pass_number = 0;
3716 reorg_pass_number < MAX_REORG_PASSES;
3717 reorg_pass_number++)
3718 {
3719 fill_simple_delay_slots (1);
3720 fill_simple_delay_slots (0);
3721 if (!targetm.no_speculation_in_delay_slots_p ())
3722 fill_eager_delay_slots ();
3723 relax_delay_slots (first);
3724 }
3725
3726 /* If we made an end of function label, indicate that it is now
3727 safe to delete it by undoing our prior adjustment to LABEL_NUSES.
3728 If it is now unused, delete it. */
3729 if (function_return_label && --LABEL_NUSES (function_return_label) == 0)
3730 delete_related_insns (function_return_label);
3731 if (function_simple_return_label
3732 && --LABEL_NUSES (function_simple_return_label) == 0)
3733 delete_related_insns (function_simple_return_label);
3734
3735 need_return_insns = false;
3736 need_return_insns |= targetm.have_return () && function_return_label != 0;
3737 need_return_insns |= (targetm.have_simple_return ()
3738 && function_simple_return_label != 0);
3739 if (need_return_insns)
3740 make_return_insns (first);
3741
3742 /* Delete any USE insns made by update_block; subsequent passes don't need
3743 them or know how to deal with them. */
3744 for (insn = first; insn; insn = next)
3745 {
3746 next = NEXT_INSN (insn);
3747
3748 if (NONJUMP_INSN_P (insn) && GET_CODE (PATTERN (insn)) == USE
3749 && INSN_P (XEXP (PATTERN (insn), 0)))
3750 next = delete_related_insns (insn);
3751 }
3752
3753 obstack_free (&unfilled_slots_obstack, unfilled_firstobj);
3754
3755 /* It is not clear why the line below is needed, but it does seem to be. */
3756 unfilled_firstobj = XOBNEWVAR (&unfilled_slots_obstack, rtx, 0);
3757
3758 if (dump_file)
3759 {
3760 int i, j, need_comma;
3761 int total_delay_slots[MAX_DELAY_HISTOGRAM + 1];
3762 int total_annul_slots[MAX_DELAY_HISTOGRAM + 1];
3763
3764 for (reorg_pass_number = 0;
3765 reorg_pass_number < MAX_REORG_PASSES;
3766 reorg_pass_number++)
3767 {
3768 fprintf (dump_file, ";; Reorg pass #%d:\n", reorg_pass_number + 1);
3769 for (i = 0; i < NUM_REORG_FUNCTIONS; i++)
3770 {
3771 need_comma = 0;
3772 fprintf (dump_file, ";; Reorg function #%d\n", i);
3773
3774 fprintf (dump_file, ";; %d insns needing delay slots\n;; ",
3775 num_insns_needing_delays[i][reorg_pass_number]);
3776
3777 for (j = 0; j < MAX_DELAY_HISTOGRAM + 1; j++)
3778 if (num_filled_delays[i][j][reorg_pass_number])
3779 {
3780 if (need_comma)
3781 fprintf (dump_file, ", ");
3782 need_comma = 1;
3783 fprintf (dump_file, "%d got %d delays",
3784 num_filled_delays[i][j][reorg_pass_number], j);
3785 }
3786 fprintf (dump_file, "\n");
3787 }
3788 }
3789 memset (total_delay_slots, 0, sizeof total_delay_slots);
3790 memset (total_annul_slots, 0, sizeof total_annul_slots);
3791 for (insn = first; insn; insn = NEXT_INSN (insn))
3792 {
3793 if (! insn->deleted ()
3794 && NONJUMP_INSN_P (insn)
3795 && GET_CODE (PATTERN (insn)) != USE
3796 && GET_CODE (PATTERN (insn)) != CLOBBER)
3797 {
3798 if (GET_CODE (PATTERN (insn)) == SEQUENCE)
3799 {
3800 rtx control;
3801 j = XVECLEN (PATTERN (insn), 0) - 1;
3802 if (j > MAX_DELAY_HISTOGRAM)
3803 j = MAX_DELAY_HISTOGRAM;
3804 control = XVECEXP (PATTERN (insn), 0, 0);
3805 if (JUMP_P (control) && INSN_ANNULLED_BRANCH_P (control))
3806 total_annul_slots[j]++;
3807 else
3808 total_delay_slots[j]++;
3809 }
3810 else if (num_delay_slots (insn) > 0)
3811 total_delay_slots[0]++;
3812 }
3813 }
3814 fprintf (dump_file, ";; Reorg totals: ");
3815 need_comma = 0;
3816 for (j = 0; j < MAX_DELAY_HISTOGRAM + 1; j++)
3817 {
3818 if (total_delay_slots[j])
3819 {
3820 if (need_comma)
3821 fprintf (dump_file, ", ");
3822 need_comma = 1;
3823 fprintf (dump_file, "%d got %d delays", total_delay_slots[j], j);
3824 }
3825 }
3826 fprintf (dump_file, "\n");
3827
3828 if (ANNUL_IFTRUE_SLOTS || ANNUL_IFFALSE_SLOTS)
3829 {
3830 fprintf (dump_file, ";; Reorg annuls: ");
3831 need_comma = 0;
3832 for (j = 0; j < MAX_DELAY_HISTOGRAM + 1; j++)
3833 {
3834 if (total_annul_slots[j])
3835 {
3836 if (need_comma)
3837 fprintf (dump_file, ", ");
3838 need_comma = 1;
3839 fprintf (dump_file, "%d got %d delays", total_annul_slots[j], j);
3840 }
3841 }
3842 fprintf (dump_file, "\n");
3843 }
3844
3845 fprintf (dump_file, "\n");
3846 }
3847
3848 if (!sibling_labels.is_empty ())
3849 {
3850 update_alignments (sibling_labels);
3851 sibling_labels.release ();
3852 }
3853
3854 free_resource_info ();
3855 free (uid_to_ruid);
3856 crtl->dbr_scheduled_p = true;
3857}
3858
3859/* Run delay slot optimization. */
3860static unsigned int
3861rest_of_handle_delay_slots (void)
3862{
3863 if (DELAY_SLOTS)
3864 dbr_schedule (get_insns ());
3865
3866 return 0;
3867}
